Vice President Biden spoke with Syrian Opposition Coalition President Moaz al-Khatib regarding the upcoming Friends of the Syrian People ministerial in Rome. Biden expressed his support for the Coalition's attendance and emphasized the importance of the meeting as an opportunity for the Coalition to share their views on the situation in Syria and discuss ways to provide assistance to the opposition and support to the Syrian people. Biden also highlighted President Obama's commitment to a political transition in Syria towards a democratic government that protects the rights of all citizens. He commended President Khatib and the SOC for their courage and expressed his desire to maintain contact.